All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Benchmark
Defines a planning problem and reasonable limits on the search to solve it.
CSVReportPrinter
A report printer that writes the various tables in a report to CSV (comma separated value) files.
CSVTablePrinter
Prints a table to a CSV (comma separated value) file.
HTMLReportPrinter
A report printer that writes a report to an HTML file.
Main
Defines the suite of benchmark problems and a set of planners, runs each planner on each problem, and outputs the results.
Report
A report is a collection of information, mostly organized into tables, about the results of testing many planners on many benchmark problems.
ReportPrinter
Print the report produced by the main class in one of several formats.
Settings
Important settings.
Statistic<N extends Number>
A statistic is a calculation to be performed on a collection of numeric values.
Table
A table is a way to store data in cells that are organized into labeled and numbered rows and columns.
Table.Group<S extends Table.Sequence>
A group of sequences of the same type.
Table.Sequence
The parent class of Table.Column and Table.Row that represents a labeled, order sequence of cells.
TestSuite
Each test in a test suite represents one run of one planner on one benchmark problem; the suite coordinates some number of threads to run tests in parallel.
TextReportPrinter
A report printer that writes a report in plain text.
VerificationHeuristic
A heuristic function used to help a heuristic progression planner reproduce a given solution by assigning an infinite cost to all actions not in a given solution.
VerificationHeuristic.Factory
A factory used to create verification heuristics.
